Serhiy Haidai, the regional governor of Luhansk, said Russia had lost hundreds of fighters during battles over the remaining Ukrainian-controlled parts of the city. The UK Ministry of Defence added in its latest intelligence update that Battalion Tactical Groups, which usually contain between 600 and 800 soldiers, have been reduced to just 30 troops. It said: “Russia’s combat force in the Donbas is highly likely to be operating in increasingly ad hoc and severely undermanned grouping". FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...